properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 12 at 8:34PM EST by NWS Peachtree City GA
properties.description:
At 833 PM EST...a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Kimball to near Woodville...and moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...40 mph wind and heavy rain.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light...unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Some locations in the path of these storms include
Trenton, Rossville, Lookout Mountain, Rising Fawn, Cole City,
Wildwood, Fairview, Stephensville, Chattanooga  Valley, New England,
Morganville, Hooker, Cloudland Canyon State Park and Cooper Heights.
properties.instruction:
People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. Motorists should
slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.
